      {
        "id": "prose.delivery-path",
        "md": "Notifications are written once by the API and fanned out over two channels: a WebSocket push for connected clients, and a poll-on-mount fallback for cold loads. The client never writes notification state directly — it only acknowledges reads.",
        "receipts": []
      },
      {
        "id": "prose.storage-model",
        "md": "Events are stored append-only in a `notifications` table; read state is a separate `notification_reads` join table so marking-as-read never mutates the event row.",
